{
    "attributes": {
        "action": "Ban the sale of confectionery at the checkout in all UK shops",
        "additional_details": "The obesity crisis that the UK is facing is unprecedented. To tackle this issue, more preventative measures ought to be taken. This petition offers such an idea. A simple idea, but one that can make a difference.\r\nReferences: \r\nBBC programme - Britain's Fat Fight with Hugh Fearnley-Whittingstall\r\nArticle: http://www.bbc.co.uk/news/health-43838655\r\nNHS on obesity: https://www.nhs.uk/conditions/obesity/\r\nFind out your BMI: http://www.bbc.co.uk/news/health-43697948\r\nSee also NHS Digital UK obesity stats.",
        "background": "The UK is facing a huge obesity crisis, which is placing increasing pressure on the NHS. This petition calls for a ban on the sale of confectionery at the checkout in all UK shops (excluding confectionery shops) to stop consumers impulse buying confectionery they would otherwise not have bought.",
